cs.CV, cs.CR, cs.LG, cs.MM, cs.HC 

This paper is primarily focused on face recognition accuracy, which falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. The investigation into differences in accuracy between African-American and Caucasian image cohorts also involves issues of bias and fairness, which could fall under the sub-categories of cryptography and security (cs.CR) and human-computer interaction (cs.HC). The use of ROC curves and statistical analysis suggests a focus on machine learning (cs.LG) and multimedia (cs.MM) sub-categories.
